  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed shopfront, by reason of inappropriate design and material would harm the appearance of the host building and fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the Hoxton Street Conservation Area and streetscene, to the detriment of the visual amenity of the host building and surrounding streetscape. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the recommendations of the Hackney Shopfront Design Guide.",
    "The proposed hot food takeaway, by reason of its close proximity to nearby schools, would contribute to and have an adverse impact upon rising levels of childhood obesity in the borough,&amp;nbsp; contrary to policy LP9(Health and Wellbeing) and LP39 (Over-Concentration Of Uses) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020)."
  ],
